HEADWORD: Nonagenarian
<hw>Non`a*ge*na"ri*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nonagenarius</ets> containing, or consisting of, ninety, fr.
<ets>nonageni</ets> ninety each; akin to <ets>novem</ets> nine.]</ety>
<def>A person ninety years old.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

